records.descr: DE not competent to stand trial, case suspended

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Allante Jovan Stubbs Harlston in court with attorney Corey R. Flynn.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  Case in court with defendant's cases 21CM2162/2969/4115 & 22CM447.  Court finds that competency is raised on all the cases with defense in agreement.  Competency hearing proceeded. Parties in receipt of examiner's report. Defense has challenged Dr. Pankiewicz's report.  Parties stipulate to Dr. Pankiewicz's qualifications to testify as an expert in the field of psychology.   Sworn for the State:  Dr. Pankiewicz.  Testimony closed.  Arguments heard. After review of all evidence, report and testimony of Dr. Pankiewicz, Court finds the defendant lacks substantial capacity to understand court proceedings or to assist in his own defense.  Court orders proceedings suspended.   Court ordered defendant committed to the Department of Health and Family Services for Institutional Care in order to restore competency within the statutory time frame . The Court does not authorize DHS to administer medications at this time.  Order of Commitment signed and filed.  Defendant is REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department for transportation to the designated facility. FORTHWITH. 
Court orders case adjourned  back to Branch 37 for Competency Review Hearing  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for June 7, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
